{"_id":"ak9Gz7zi41IOXlIQ","name":"Tools","content":"<p>A tool helps you to do something you couldn't otherwise do, such as craft or repair an item, forge a document, or pick a lock. Your, class, background, or feats give you proficiency with certain tools. Proficiency with a tool allows you to add your proficiency bonus to any ability check you make using that tool. Tool use is not tied to a single ability, since proficiency with a tool represents broader knowledge of its use. For example, the DM might ask you to make a Dexterity check to carve a fine detail with your woodcarver's tools, or a Strength check to make something out of a particularly hard wood.</p>\n<table border=\"1\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"3\">Tools</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Item</td>\n<td>Cost</td>\n<td>Weight</td>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"background-color:#cccccc\">\n<td colspan=\"3\"><em>Artisan's Tools</em></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>    @Compendium[5e-complete.5e-items.JK0OX6MAQvfpdSAw]{Alchemist's Supplies}</td>\n<td>50 gp</td>\n<td>8 lb.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>    @Compendium[5e-complete.5e-items.2P8PtztqUc5jzUiI]{Brewer's Supplies}</td>\n<td>20 gp</td>\n<td>9 lb.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>    @Compendium[5e-complete.5e-items.ZPVuBGvk3pZrQPXS]{Calligrapher's Supplies}</td>\n<td>10 gp</td>\n<td>5 lb.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>    @Compendium[5e-complete.5e-items.5H49JjP6aNGKbwe0]{Carpenter's Tools}</td>\n<td>8 gp</td>\n<td>6 lb.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>    @Compendium[5e-complete.5e-items.LQJM6oYihVFTfreA]{Cartographer's Tools}</td>\n<td>15 gp</td>\n<td>6 lb.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>    @Compendium[5e-complete.5e-items.QrupR3Hd1yrvEAHC]{Cobbler's Tools}</td>\n<td>5 gp</td>\n<td>5 lb.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>    @Compendium[5e-complete.5e-items.5GzYgNE77Inmnipm]{Cook's Utensils}</td>\n<td>1 gp</td>\n<td>8 lb.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>    @Compendium[5e-complete.5e-items.Ho0Mtx8c64HgvPRs]{Glassblower's Tools}</td>\n<td>30 gp</td>\n<td>5 lb.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>    @Compendium[5e-complete.5e